properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 15 at 12:06AM CST until January 15 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...NEXT ROUND OF SNOW EARLY THIS MORNING THROUGH THIS EVENING...

.The next round of snow will spread across the Northland tonight
and last into Wednesday. The heaviest snow will fall from the
Brainerd Lakes area eastward to the I-35 corridor, including the
Twin Ports, and into much of northwest Wisconsin. Snowfall totals
of 2 to 4 inches are expected across the Minnesota portion of the
Advisory with isolated higher amounts. Northwest Wisconsin will
see 3 to 5 inches of accumulation with isolated higher amounts,
highest across Douglas, Bayfield, Ashland and Iron Counties. Snow
will taper off from west to east Wednesday afternoon.

* WHAT...Snow, with snow accumulation of 2 to 4 inches.

* WHERE...Pine, South Cass, Crow Wing, Northern Aitkin, South
Aitkin, Carlton and South St. Louis, South Itasca and North
Cass Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Fond du
Lac Band and the Mille Lacs Band, East Lake, Lena Lake,
Hinckley and, Big Sandy Lake areas.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions, including during the
morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
